meanings.definition: A taxonomic subclass within the class Ascidiacea – tunicates that have a single branchial aperture.
meanings.english_definition: A taxonomic subclass within the class Ascidiacea – tunicates that have a single branchial aperture.

etymology.value: From the order name Monascidia + -ae (standard zoological suffix forming names of subclasses).

usage_notes.explanation: This term is primarily used in scientific and taxonomic contexts.
